Defence Minister Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula. JOHANNESBURG - Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Defence wants answers from Minister Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula.
The committee has agreed to a DA request to have Mapisa-Nqakula account for the ANC's use of an airforce jet. READ: ATM asks PP to probe Ramaphosa's role in ANC trip to Zim The DA wants her to explain why she allowed the flight to Zimbabwe and whether Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula had granted the delegation permission to travel, during the lockdown. The ANC is to reimburse the state for the cost of the flight and President Cyril Ramaphosa has reprimanded Mapisa-Nqakula.